The packages 'numpy' and 'matplotlib' are required to run these auxiliary programs.

decompress.py:
 Command line argument 1: the path to the input directory containing the compressed data.
 Command line argument 2: (optional) the path to an existing directory where the decompressed data will be saved.
 	      	       	  If omitted, the decompressed data will be saved in the same directory as the input (argument 1).

plot_lcurves.py:
 Command line argument 1: the path to the directory containing the *decompressed* data.
 	      	       	  A new directory named 'plots' will be created inside this directory containing the plotted light curves.
